## **2. Builtin Execution (Parent Process)**

Execute these **without forking** (parent must be modified):

| Builtin | Why Parent? | Effect |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| `cd` | Changes shell's working dir | Must run in parent |
| `export VAR=val` | Modifies shell environment | Must run in parent |
| `unset VAR` | Removes env variable | Must run in parent |
| `exit [code]` | Terminates shell | Must run in parent |
| `echo` | Output only | Can be child, but custom impl |
| `pwd` | Read only | Can be child, but custom impl |
| env | Print environment | Can be child, but custom impl |

Implementation:
```c
int builtin_cd(char **args, t_env *env)
{
    if (chdir(args[1]) == -1)
        return (1);  // error
    return (0);      // success
}
```

