## **7. Input/Output Redirections**

Handle `>`, `>>`, `<`, `2>`, etc.:

```bash
ls > file.txt          # REDIRECT_OUT (overwrite)
ls >> file.txt         # REDIRECT_APPEND (append)
cat < input.txt        # REDIRECT_IN (read from file)
ls 2> error.log        # REDIRECT_ERR (stderr)
ls 2>&1                # Redirect stderr to stdout
```

Implementation (in child before execve):
```c
if (cmd->redirect_out)
{
    int fd = open(cmd->redirect_out, O_WRONLY | O_CREAT | O_TRUNC);
    dup2(fd, STDOUT_FILENO);
    close(fd);
}
if (cmd->redirect_in)
{
    int fd = open(cmd->redirect_in, O_RDONLY);
    dup2(fd, STDIN_FILENO);
    close(fd);
}
execve(cmd_path, args, environ);
```

