## **9. Conditional Execution (`&&`, `||`)**

Run next command based on previous exit status:

```bash
ls && echo "success"    # Run echo only if ls succeeds (status=0)
ls || echo "failed"     # Run echo only if ls fails (status!=0)
```

Implementation:
```c
for (each cmd in cmd_list)
{
    exit_status = execute_command(cmd);
   
    if (cmd->next_operator == AND && exit_status != 0)
        break;  // Skip rest
    if (cmd->next_operator == OR && exit_status == 0)
        break;  // Skip rest
}
```

