## **13. Multiple Pipes (N Commands)**

Chain multiple pipes:

```bash
ls | grep .c | wc -l
```

Implementation:
```c
int execute_pipe_chain(t_cmd *cmd_list)
{
    int i = 0;
    int fd[2];
    pid_t *pids;
    int cmd_count = count_commands(cmd_list);

    pids = malloc(sizeof(pid_t) * cmd_count);

    // For each command
    for (i = 0; cmd_list; cmd_list = cmd_list->next, i++)
    {
        if (cmd_list->next)  // Not last command
            pipe(fd);

        pids[i] = fork();
        if (pids[i] == 0)  // Child
        {
            if (i > 0)  // Not first: read from prev pipe
                dup2(prev_fd[0], STDIN_FILENO);
            if (cmd_list->next)  // Not last: write to next pipe
                dup2(fd[1], STDOUT_FILENO);
           
            execute_external(cmd_list);
        }
        prev_fd = fd;  // Save for next iteration
    }

    // Parent waits for all
    for (i = 0; i < cmd_count; i++)
        waitpid(pids[i], NULL, 0);

    return (0);
}
```

