## **14. Background Execution (`&`)**

Run command and return prompt immediately:

```bash
sleep 100 &
```

Implementation:
```c
if (cmd->is_background)
{
    pid = fork();
    if (pid == 0)
        execute_external(cmd);
    // Parent returns immediately, don't waitpid()
}
else
{
    pid = fork();
    if (pid == 0)
        execute_external(cmd);
    waitpid(pid, &status, 0);  // Wait
}
```

